headline: DHR Q3 2025 Deep Dive: Bioprocessing, Diagnostics, and Productivity Initiatives Amid Policy Shifts
summary: Diversified science and technology company Danaher (NYSE:DHR) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 4.4% year on year to $6.05 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $6.70 billion was less impressive, coming in 4.7% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.89 per share was 9.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
